'''Craythur''' is an [[Ireland|Irish]] term for [[whiskey]]. The term is analogous to ''uisge beatha'' (the ''water of life'') in [[Scottish Gaelic language|Scots Gaelic]]. 'A drop of the craythur' is a popular if old expression.  origins of the word are from large iron age bowls from which alcohol was served.


